he University of Michigan.\nTim has actively invested in Web3 since 2014, advising and supporting web3 gaming startups.\n\nIn the event that one or both members are not reconfirmed, there will be a nomination period and election to fill the empty Council seats. The council is not expected to pause any operational votes or decision making while the seats are filled.\n\nElections (if required)\nNovember 1 - Close of Council Nominations\nNovember 6 -AMA with Council candidates\nNovember 7 - Start of snapshot vote for electing one or two open Council positions \nNovember 14 - Conclusion of snapshot and deemed election of top one or two candidates respectively",
