ader at Goldman Sachs, Mona was promoted to Vice President by the age of 26 and made the “Top 30 under 30” list in Trader Magazine in 2008 and Forbes Magazine in 2011 after profitably trading the 2008 and 2011 crashes. She moved to Geneva-based macro fund Jabre Capital in 2011, before deciding in 2014 that the future of finance lay in blockchain technology.\n\nAinsley To (PhD, CFA) is Head of Asset Management. His background includes roles at investment consultant Stamford Associates and over a decade as Head of Multi-Asset at Credo, where he was featured in Citywire’s Wealth Manager Top 100 in 2019 for overseeing selection & monitoring of third party funds. Ainsley has also held crypto research roles at Messari and digital asset prime broker Genesis. Ainsley is a CFA charterholder, and holds a PhD in Finance from EDHEC Business School, where he published research on crypto asset pricing.\n\nGabriel Rocheleau leads DeFi R&D at Avantgarde. With a solid foundation in Actuarial Sciences, he excels in his roles as a smart contracts developer, a full-stack developer and an Ethereum Core Developer.\n\nSpike Watanabe graduated from University College London with a degree in Economics. He has worked in investment and commercial banks, valuation consultancies and private equity to oversee private mergers and acquisition deals with total value in excess of 2bn USD. He was actively involved within blockchain markets since 2016, conducting research and running his own investments.\n\nPricing\n\n$75,000/ year + $10,000 per service provider\n\n% of budget this contract constitutes: Less than 10%, if affiliates are included less than 3%\n\nProof of Work\n\nArbitrum Treasury & Sustainability research  https://forum.arbitrum.foundation/t/arbitrum-treasury-and-sustainability-research-risk-reduction-in-dao-treasuries/20662\n\nApecoin DAO Treasury & Sustainability Planning\nhttps://drive.google.com/file/d/1lZxt48D-7gBAN01qOB_DA6ECn5Tvp4yP/view \n\nNexus Dashboard\nhttps://app.enzyme.fi